and mobile policemen have been drafted to the scene of the incident located close to the Central Motor Park, in Ekeki, the state capital. When contacted the spokesman of the Bayelsa State Police Command, ASP Asinim Butswat, said he was trying to get confirmation from the Divisional Police Officer, DPO, of Ekeki Police Division as at the time of filing this report. Vanguard News Nigeria. The Police Command in Ekiti has arrested one of its men, Cpl. Ayodele Famodimu, who allegedly shot dead a commercial driver on Tuesday. December 13, 2017 In "News" This is the story of how a policeman senselessly killed a woman with an seven-month pregnancy in broad day light, leading to the burning of a bank and cars. February 5, 2011 In "Metro" MPAPE, a suburb in the nationâ€™s Capital City, Abuja was Monday thrown into confusion following the shooting to death of a pregnant woman in front of a Bank in the area by a mobile policeman. January 31, 2011 In "News"